<Link id="l00409" /><CodeLine lineNumber="409"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// isRenamable - Returns true if this register may be renamed, i.e. it does</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00410" /><CodeLine lineNumber="410"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// not generate a value that is somehow read in a way that is not represented</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00411" /><CodeLine lineNumber="411"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// by the Machine IR (e.g. to meet an ABI or ISA requirement).  This is only</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00412" /><CodeLine lineNumber="412"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// valid on physical register operands.  Virtual registers are assumed to</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00413" /><CodeLine lineNumber="413"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// always be renamable regardless of the value of this field.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00414" /><CodeLine lineNumber="414"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00415" /><CodeLine lineNumber="415"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// Operands that are renamable can freely be changed to any other register</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00416" /><CodeLine lineNumber="416"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// that is a member of the register class returned by</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00417" /><CodeLine lineNumber="417"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// MI-&gt;getRegClassConstraint().</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00418" /><CodeLine lineNumber="418"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00419" /><CodeLine lineNumber="419"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// isRenamable can return false for several different reasons:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00420" /><CodeLine lineNumber="420"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00421" /><CodeLine lineNumber="421"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// - ABI constraints (since liveness is not always precisely modeled).  We</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00422" /><CodeLine lineNumber="422"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   conservatively handle these cases by setting all physical register</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00423" /><CodeLine lineNumber="423"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   operands that didn’t start out as virtual regs to not be renamable.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00424" /><CodeLine lineNumber="424"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   Also any physical register operands created after register allocation or</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00425" /><CodeLine lineNumber="425"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   whose register is changed after register allocation will not be</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00426" /><CodeLine lineNumber="426"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   renamable.  This state is tracked in the MachineOperand::IsRenamable</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00427" /><CodeLine lineNumber="427"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   bit.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00428" /><CodeLine lineNumber="428"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00429" /><CodeLine lineNumber="429"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// - Opcode/target constraints: for opcodes that have complex register class</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00430" /><CodeLine lineNumber="430"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   requirements (e.g. that depend on other operands/instructions), we set</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00431" /><CodeLine lineNumber="431"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   hasExtraSrcRegAllocReq/hasExtraDstRegAllocReq in the machine opcode</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00432" /><CodeLine lineNumber="432"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   description.  Operands belonging to instructions with opcodes that are</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00433" /><CodeLine lineNumber="433"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   marked hasExtraSrcRegAllocReq/hasExtraDstRegAllocReq return false from</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00434" /><CodeLine lineNumber="434"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   isRenamable().  Additionally, the AllowRegisterRenaming target property</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00435" /><CodeLine lineNumber="435"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   prevents any operands from being marked renamable for targets that don&#39;t</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00436" /><CodeLine lineNumber="436"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   have detailed opcode hasExtraSrcRegAllocReq/hasExtraDstRegAllocReq</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00437" /><CodeLine lineNumber="437"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   values.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00438" /><CodeLine lineNumber="438"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">bool</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machineoperand/#a8be49bc86b5d01b52b90baf1b4477667">isRenamable</a>() </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight">;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00921" /><CodeLine lineNumber="921"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// CreateRegMask - Creates a register mask operand referencing Mask.  The</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00924" /><CodeLine lineNumber="924"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00925" /><CodeLine lineNumber="925"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// A RegMask operand represents a set of non-clobbered physical registers</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00926" /><CodeLine lineNumber="926"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// on an instruction that clobbers many registers, typically a call.  The</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00927" /><CodeLine lineNumber="927"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// bit mask has a bit set for each physreg that is preserved by this</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00928" /><CodeLine lineNumber="928"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// instruction, as described in the documentation for</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00929" /><CodeLine lineNumber="929"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// TargetRegisterInfo::getCallPreservedMask().</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00930" /><CodeLine lineNumber="930"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00931" /><CodeLine lineNumber="931"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// Any physreg with a 0 bit in the mask is clobbered by the instruction.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00932" /><CodeLine lineNumber="932"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00933" /><CodeLine lineNumber="933" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machineoperand/#a4c01d756ca363aef75429d61d21c0c14"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">static</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> MachineOperand <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machineoperand/#a4c01d756ca363aef75429d61d21c0c14">CreateRegMask</a>(</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> uint32&#95;t &#42;Mask) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
